The total mass of the flask containing the nanofluid (mt
                           ) and the mass of the empty pycnometer (mpc
                           ) were utilized in the measurements conducted at temperatures of 35, 40, 45, 50, and 55°C. The test sample vials underwent temperature control through the utilization of a thermostat. Then, heated sample will be transferred to the pycnometer depicted in Fig. 7c and employed in the experiment.
